        "title": "docs(browser): note bare ws diagnostics use runtime fallback",
        "body": "## Summary\r\n\r\n  The recent fix in e25b3c60 (\"Browser/CDP: make readiness diagnostics use the same discovery-first\r\n  fallback as reachability for bare `ws://` Browserless and Browserbase CDP URLs\") aligned `openclaw\r\n  browser doctor` with the runtime's connection strategy for bare-root WebSocket CDP URLs.\r\n\r\n  The \"Direct WebSocket CDP providers → Bare WebSocket roots\" section in `docs/tools/browser.md` describes\r\n  the runtime fallback chain, but does not mention that diagnostics now follow the same chain. Users who\r\n  previously saw doctor flag a bare-root URL as unreachable while the runtime connected fine could still\r\n  wonder whether the mismatch persists.\r\n\r\n  This adds one sentence noting the parity, so anyone reading the section after the fix sees the full\r\n  picture.\r\n\r\n  ## Test plan\r\n\r\n  - [x] Docs-only change; no code touched\r\n  - [x] Confirmed against the diagnostics changes in `extensions/browser/src/browser/chrome.diagnostics.ts`\r\n   from e25b3c60\r\n",
